    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A cushioning system of cored-out hexagonal recesses developed by Reebok for use in shoes. Its honeycomb structure is made of rubbery thermoplastic urethane. Hexalite has been adapted for use as a support for wallpapers and textiles in museum display.</Note_Text>
